20 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 6, Chapter 17, Subchapter 3 is amended
21 to add an additional section to read as follows:
22 6-17-311. School chaplain — Definitions.
23 (a)(1) A public school may employ or accept as a volunteer a school
24 chaplain to provide support, services, and programs for enrolled students,
25 staff employed by the public school, and parents of enrolled students.
26 (2) A public school that chooses to employ or accept as a
27 volunteer a school chaplain under subdivision (a)(1) of this section shall
28 determine the selection criteria for the school chaplain.
29 (3) A public school may employ or accept as a volunteer more
30 than one (1) school chaplain under this section.
31 (b) A school chaplain employed by or volunteering at a public school
32 under this section is not required to be credentialed by the Department of
33 Education.
34 (c)(1) Before a public school may employ or accept as a volunteer a
35 school chaplain under this section, the public school shall require the
36 school chaplain to authorize release to the Division of Elementary and
